#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr "Theravāda Collection on Monastic Law"

#. HTML: </p><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr "Monks’ rules and their analysis"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:0.3"
msgid "Saṃ­ghā­di­sesa­kaṇḍa"
msgstr "Monks’ Suspension"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:0.4"
msgid "Bhedā­nu­vatta­ka­sikkhā­pada"
msgstr "11. The training rule on supporting a schism"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-vp-pli3.175, pts-vp-en1.304, pts-cs-bu-ss11.1, ms1V_1704 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalanda­ka­nivāpe."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Rājagaha in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrel sanctuary."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena devadatto saṃghabhedāya parakkamati cakkabhedāya."
msgstr "At that time Devadatta was pursuing schism in the Order, a break in transmission."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:1.3"
msgid "Bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "The monks were saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:1.4"
msgid "“adhammavādī devadatto, avinayavādī devadatto."
msgstr "“Devadatta doesn’t speak in accordance with the Teaching or the training."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:1.5"
msgid "Kathañhi nāma devadatto saṃghabhedāya parakkamissati cakkabhedāyā”ti."
msgstr "How can he pursue schism in the Order?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: kokāliko → kokāliko ca (bj)
#. VAR: samuddadatto → samuddadatto ca (bj)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:1.6"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, kokāliko kaṭa­modaka­tissako khaṇḍadeviyā putto samuddadatto te bhikkhū etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "But Kokālika, Kaṭamodakatissaka, Khaṇḍadeviyā-putta, and Samuddadatta said to those monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:1.7"
msgid "“māyasmanto evaṃ avacuttha."
msgstr "“Venerables, don’t say that."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:1.8"
msgid "Dhammavādī devadatto, vinayavādī devadatto."
msgstr "Devadatta does speak in accordance with the Teaching and the training."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:1.9"
msgid "Amhākañca devadatto chandañca ruciñca ādāya voharati jānāti no bhāsati amhākampetaṃ khamatī”ti."
msgstr "And he speaks with our consent and approval. He knows about us and speaks for us, and we agree to this.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:1.10"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:1.11"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:1.12"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma bhikkhū devadattassa saṃghabhedāya parakka­man­tassa anuvattakā bhavissanti vaggavādakā”ti."
msgstr "“How can these monks support Devadatta’s pursuit of schism in the Order?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, ms1V_1705 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:1.13"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū te anuvattake bhikkhū aneka­pariyā­yena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "They rebuked those monks in many ways and then told the Master. …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:1.14"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhū devadattassa saṃghabhedāya parakka­man­tassa anuvattakā honti vaggavādakā”ti?"
msgstr "He said, “Is it true, monks, that some monks support Devadatta’s pursuit of schism in the Order?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-en1.305
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:1.15"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:1.16"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha criticized them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:1.17"
msgid "kathañhi nāma te, bhikkhave, moghapurisā devadattassa saṃghabhedāya parakka­man­tassa anuvattakā bhavissanti vaggavādakā."
msgstr "Monks, how can those foolish men support Devadatta’s pursuit of schism in the Order?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:1.18"
msgid "Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:1.19"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:1.19a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc3, ms1V_1706
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:1.20"
msgid "“Tasseva kho pana bhikkhussa bhikkhū honti anuvattakā vaggavādakā eko vā dve vā tayo vā."
msgstr "‘That monk may have one, two, or three monks who take his side and support him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:1.21"
msgid "Te evaṃ vadeyyuṃ—"
msgstr "and they may say,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:1.22"
msgid "‘māyasmanto etaṃ bhikkhuṃ kiñci avacuttha."
msgstr "“Venerables, don’t correct this monk."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:1.23"
msgid "Dhammavādī ceso bhikkhu, vinayavādī ceso bhikkhu."
msgstr "He speaks in accordance with the Teaching and the training."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:1.24"
msgid "Amhākañceso bhikkhu chandañca ruciñca ādāya voharati jānāti no bhāsati amhākampetaṃ khamatī’ti,"
msgstr "And he speaks with our consent and approval. He knows about us and speaks for us, and we agree to this.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:1.25"
msgid "te bhikkhū bhikkhūhi evamassu vacanīyā—"
msgstr "The monks should say to those monks,"

#. VAR: māyasmanto → mā āyasmanto (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:1.26"
msgid "‘māyasmanto evaṃ avacuttha,"
msgstr "“Venerables, don’t say that."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:1.27"
msgid "na ceso bhikkhu dhammavādī, na ceso bhikkhu vinayavādī,"
msgstr "This monk does not speak in accordance with the Teaching or the training."

#. VAR: mā­yasman­tānampi → mā āyasmantānampi (bj, s1-3) | māyasmantānaṃ pi (pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:1.28"
msgid "­mā­yasman­tānampi saṃghabhedo ruccittha,"
msgstr "Don’t consent to schism in the Order."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:1.29"
msgid "­same­tā­yasman­tānaṃ saṃghena,"
msgstr "Stay with the Order,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:1.30"
msgid "­samaggo hi saṃgho sammodamāno avivadamāno ekuddeso phāsu viharatī’ti."
msgstr "for a united Order—in concord, in harmony, having a joint recitation—lives in comfort.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:1.31"
msgid "Evañca te bhikkhū bhikkhūhi vuccamānā tatheva paggaṇheyyuṃ, te bhikkhū bhikkhūhi yāvatatiyaṃ sama­nubhā­si­tabbā tassa paṭinissaggāya."
msgstr "If those monks still continue as before, the monks should admonish them up to three times to make them stop."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:1.32"
msgid "Yāvatatiyañce sama­nubhā­si­yamānā taṃ paṭi­nissaj­jey­yuṃ, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ,"
msgstr "If they then stop, that is good."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:1.33"
msgid "no ce paṭi­nissaj­jey­yuṃ, saṃghādiseso”ti."
msgstr "If not, they commit an offense entailing suspension.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc4, pts-cs-bu-ss11.2, ms1V_1707
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.1"
msgid "Tasseva kho panāti"
msgstr "That:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.2"
msgid "tassa saṃgha­bheda­kassa bhikkhuno."
msgstr "that monk who is pursuing schism in the Order."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc5, ms1V_1708
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.3"
msgid "Bhikkhū hontīti"
msgstr "May have […] monks:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.4"
msgid "aññe bhikkhū honti."
msgstr "may have other monks."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc6, ms1V_1709
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.5"
msgid "Anuvattakāti"
msgstr "Who take his side:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.6"
msgid "yaṃdiṭṭhiko so hoti yaṃkhantiko yaṃruciko tepi taṃdiṭṭhikā honti taṃkhantikā taṃrucikā."
msgstr "they have the same view, the same belief, the same persuasion as he does."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc7, ms1V_1710
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.7"
msgid "Vaggavādakāti"
msgstr "Who […] support him:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.8"
msgid "tassa vaṇṇāya pakkhāya ṭhitā honti."
msgstr "they take his side and are part of his group."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc8, pts-vp-pli3.176, pts-vp-en1.306, ms1V_1711
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.9"
msgid "Eko vā dve vā tayo vāti"
msgstr "One, two, or three:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.10"
msgid "eko vā hoti dve vā tayo vā."
msgstr "There is one, or two, or three."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.11"
msgid "Te evaṃ vadeyyuṃ—"
msgstr "They may say,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.12"
msgid "“māyasmanto etaṃ bhikkhuṃ kiñci avacuttha,"
msgstr "“Venerables, don’t correct this monk."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.13"
msgid "dhammavādī ceso bhikkhu, vinayavādī ceso bhikkhu,"
msgstr "He speaks in accordance with the Teaching and the training."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.14"
msgid "amhākañceso bhikkhu chandañca ruciñca ādāya voharati jānāti no bhāsati amhākampetaṃ khamatī”ti."
msgstr "And he speaks with our consent and approval. He knows about us and speaks for us, and we agree to this.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc9, ms1V_1712
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.15"
msgid "Te bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Those monks:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.16"
msgid "ye te anuvattakā bhikkhū."
msgstr "those monks who take his side."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc10, ms1V_1713
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.17"
msgid "Bhikkhūhīti"
msgstr "The monks:"

#. HTML: </span></p><div class="gloss"><p>
#. REF: ms1V_1714 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.18"
msgid "aññehi bhikkhūhi."
msgstr "Other monks,"

#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.19"
msgid "Ye passanti ye suṇanti tehi vattabbā—"
msgstr "those who see it or hear about it. They should say,"

#. HTML: <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.20"
msgid "“māyasmanto evaṃ avacuttha."
msgstr "“Venerables, don’t say that."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.21"
msgid "Na ceso bhikkhu dhammavādī, na ceso bhikkhu vinayavādī."
msgstr "This monk does not speak in accordance with the Teaching or the training."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.22"
msgid "­Mā­yasman­tānampi saṃghabhedo ruccittha."
msgstr "Don’t consent to schism in the Order."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.23"
msgid "Same­tā­yasman­tānaṃ saṃghena."
msgstr "Stay with the Order,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.24"
msgid "Samaggo hi saṃgho sammodamāno avivadamāno ekuddeso phāsu viharatī”ti."
msgstr "for a united Order—in concord, in harmony, having a joint recitation—lives in comfort.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.25"
msgid "Dutiyampi vattabbā."
msgstr "And they should say this a second"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.26"
msgid "Tatiyampi vattabbā."
msgstr "and a third time."

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.27"
msgid "Sace paṭi­nissaj­janti, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ;"
msgstr "If they stop, that is good."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.28"
msgid "no ce paṭi­nissaj­janti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If they do not stop, they commit an offense of wrong conduct."

#. HTML: <span class="subrule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.29"
msgid "Sutvā na vadanti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If those who hear about it do not say anything, they commit an offense of wrong conduct."

#. HTML: </span></p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.30"
msgid "Te bhikkhū saṃgha­majjhampi ākaḍḍhitvā vattabbā—"
msgstr "Those monks, even if they have to be dragged into the middle of the Order, should be to spoken to thus:"

#. HTML: <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.31"
msgid "“māyasmanto evaṃ avacuttha."
msgstr "“Venerables, don’t say that."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.32"
msgid "Na ceso bhikkhu dhammavādī, na ceso bhikkhu vinayavādī."
msgstr "This monk does not speak in accordance with the Teaching or the training."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.33"
msgid "­Mā­yasman­tānampi saṃghabhedo ruccittha."
msgstr "Don’t consent to schism in the Order."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.34"
msgid "Same­tā­yasman­tānaṃ saṃghena."
msgstr "Stay with the Order,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.35"
msgid "Samaggo hi saṃgho sammodamāno avivadamāno ekuddeso phāsu viharatī”ti."
msgstr "for a united Order—in concord, in harmony, having a joint recitation—lives in comfort.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.36"
msgid "Dutiyampi vattabbā."
msgstr "They should say this a second"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.37"
msgid "Tatiyampi vattabbā."
msgstr "and a third time."

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.38"
msgid "Sace paṭi­nissaj­janti, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ;"
msgstr "If they stop, that is good."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.39"
msgid "no ce paṭi­nissaj­janti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If they do not stop, they commit an offense of wrong conduct."

#. HTML: </p></div><p><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.40"
msgid "Te bhikkhū sama­nubhā­si­tabbā."
msgstr "Should admonish them:"

#. HTML: </span></p><div class="gloss"><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.41"
msgid "“Evañca pana, bhikkhave, sama­nubhā­si­tabbā."
msgstr "“And, monks, they should be admonished in this way."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.42"
msgid "Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṃgho ñāpetabbo—"
msgstr "A competent and capable monk should inform the Order:"

#. HTML: </p><div class="kamma"><p>
#. REF: sc12, ms1V_1715 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.43"
msgid "‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "‘Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.44"
msgid "Itthannāmo ca itthanāmo ca bhikkhū itthannāmassa bhikkhuno saṃghabhedāya parakka­man­tassa anuvattakā vaggavādakā."
msgstr "Monks so-and-so and so-and-so are taking sides with and supporting monk so-and-so who is pursuing schism in the Order."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.45"
msgid "Te taṃ vatthuṃ na paṭi­nissaj­janti."
msgstr "They are not stopping that activity."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.46"
msgid "Yadi saṃghassa pattakallaṃ, saṃgho itthannāmañca itthannāmañca bhikkhū samanubhāseyya tassa vatthussa paṭinissaggāya."
msgstr "If it seems appropriate to the Order, the Order should admonish them to make them stop."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.47"
msgid "Esā ñatti."
msgstr "This is the motion."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13, ms1V_1716 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.48"
msgid "Suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.49"
msgid "Itthannāmo ca itthannāmo ca bhikkhū itthannāmassa bhikkhuno saṃghabhedāya parakka­man­tassa anuvattakā vaggavādakā."
msgstr "Monks so-and-so and so-and-so are taking sides with and supporting monk so-and-so who is pursuing schism in the Order."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.50"
msgid "Te taṃ vatthuṃ na paṭi­nissaj­janti."
msgstr "They are not stopping that activity."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.51"
msgid "Saṃgho itthannāmañca itthannāmañca bhikkhū samanubhāsati tassa vatthussa paṭinissaggāya."
msgstr "The Order admonishes them to make them stop."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.52"
msgid "Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa ca itthannāmassa ca bhikkhūnaṃ samanubhāsanā tassa vatthussa paṭinissaggāya, so tuṇhassa;"
msgstr "Any monk who approves of admonishing them to make them stop should remain silent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.53"
msgid "yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya."
msgstr "Any monk who does not approve should speak up."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14, ms1V_1717 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.54"
msgid "Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi … pe …"
msgstr "A second time …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.55"
msgid "tatiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi—"
msgstr "A third time I speak on this matter:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.56"
msgid "suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.57"
msgid "Itthannāmo ca itthannāmo ca bhikkhū itthannāmassa bhikkhuno saṃghabhedāya parakka­man­tassa anuvattakā vaggavādakā."
msgstr "Monks so-and-so and so-and-so are taking sides with and supporting monk so-and-so who is pursuing schism in the Order."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.58"
msgid "Te taṃ vatthuṃ na paṭi­nissaj­janti."
msgstr "They are not stopping that activity."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.59"
msgid "Saṃgho itthannāmañca itthannāmañca bhikkhū samanubhāsati tassa vatthussa paṭinissaggāya."
msgstr "The Order admonishes them to make them stop."

#. REF: pts-vp-en1.307
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.60"
msgid "Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa ca itthannāmassa ca bhikkhūnaṃ samanubhāsanā tassa vatthussa paṭinissaggāya, so tuṇhassa;"
msgstr "Any monk who approves of admonishing them to make them stop should remain silent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.61"
msgid "yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya."
msgstr "Any monk who does not approve should speak up."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc15, ms1V_1718 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.62"
msgid "Samanubhaṭṭhā saṃghena itthannāmo ca itthannāmo ca bhikkhū tassa vatthussa paṭinissaggāya."
msgstr "The monks so-and-so and so-and-so have been admonished by the Order to make them stop that activity."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.63"
msgid "Khamati saṃghassa, tasmā tuṇhī,"
msgstr "The Order approves and is therefore silent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.64"
msgid "evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti."
msgstr "I will remember it thus.’”"

#. HTML: </p></div></div><hr><p>
#. REF: sc16, ms1V_1719 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.65"
msgid "Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ,"
msgstr "After the motion, they commit an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.66"
msgid "dvīhi kammavācāhi thullaccayā,"
msgstr "After each of the first two announcements, they commit a serious offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.67"
msgid "kamma­vācā­pari­yosāne āpatti saṃ­ghā­di­sesassa."
msgstr "When the last announcement is finished, they commit an offense entailing suspension."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.68"
msgid "Saṃghādisesaṃ ajjhā­pajjan­tānaṃ ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ, dvīhi kammavācāhi thullaccayā paṭippas­sam­bhanti."
msgstr "For those who commit the offense entailing suspension, the offense of wrong conduct and the serious offenses are annulled."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.69"
msgid "Dve tayo ekato sama­nubhā­si­tabbā, taduttari na sama­nubhā­si­tabbā."
msgstr "Two or three can be admonished together, but not more than that."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc17, ms1V_1720
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.70"
msgid "Saṃghādisesoti"
msgstr "They commit an offense entailing suspension:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:2.71"
msgid "… pe … tenapi vuccati “saṃghādiseso”ti."
msgstr "… Therefore, too, it is called “an offense entailing suspension.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:3.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. VAR: dhamma­kamma­saññī → dhamma­kamma­saññino (si)
#. REF: sc18, pts-vp-pli3.177, pts-cs-bu-ss11.3.1, ms1V_1721
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:3.1.1"
msgid "Dhammakamme dhamma­kamma­saññī na paṭi­nissaj­janti, āpatti saṃ­ghā­di­sesassa."
msgstr "If it is a legitimate procedure, and they perceive it as legitimate, but they do not stop, they commit an offense entailing suspension."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc19, ms1V_1722 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:3.1.2"
msgid "Dhammakamme vematikā na paṭi­nissaj­janti, āpatti saṃ­ghā­di­sesassa."
msgstr "If it is a legitimate procedure, but they are unsure if it is, and they do not stop, they commit an offense entailing suspension."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc20, ms1V_1723 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:3.1.3"
msgid "Dhammakamme adhamma­kamma­saññī na paṭi­nissaj­janti, āpatti saṃ­ghā­di­sesassa."
msgstr "If it is a legitimate procedure, but they perceive it as illegitimate, and they do not stop, they commit an offense entailing suspension."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc21, ms1V_1724 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:3.1.4"
msgid "Adhammakamme dhamma­kamma­saññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is an illegitimate procedure, but they perceive it as legitimate, they commit an offense of wrong conduct."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc22, ms1V_1725 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:3.1.5"
msgid "Adhammakamme vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is an illegitimate procedure, but they are unsure if it is, they commit an offense of wrong conduct."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc23, ms1V_1726 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:3.1.6"
msgid "Adhammakamme adhamma­kamma­saññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is an illegitimate procedure, and they perceive it as illegitimate, they commit an offense of wrong conduct."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:3.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc24, pts-cs-bu-ss11.3.2, pts-vp-en1.308, ms1V_1727 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:3.2.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:3.2.2"
msgid "asama­nu­bhāsan­tā­naṃ,"
msgstr "if they have not been admonished;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:3.2.3"
msgid "paṭi­nissaj­jan­tānaṃ,"
msgstr "if they stop;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:3.2.4"
msgid "ummattakānaṃ,"
msgstr "if they are insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:3.2.5"
msgid "khittacittānaṃ,"
msgstr "if they are deranged;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:3.2.6"
msgid "vedanāṭṭānaṃ,"
msgstr "if they are overwhelmed by pain;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:3.2.7"
msgid "ādi­kammi­kā­nanti."
msgstr "if they are the first offenders."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc25, ms1V_1728 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss11:3.2.8"
msgid "Bhedā­nu­vatta­ka­sikkhā­padaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ ekādasamaṃ."
msgstr "The eleventh rule, the training rule on supporting a schism, is finished."
